node.text:
To defeat an enemy against humanity, it takes all of us. June 6, 1944, also known as D-Day, was a crucial moment in the second World War. It took strategy, strength, and most of all, selflessness to achieve victory, but none of it could have come without sacrifice. We remember D-Day and the men who gave it their all for a better world tomorrow.

Happy #PresidentsDay from the ones keeping the President on the move! Here are some fun facts about the world’s fanciest, most functional ride: Air Force One. 
 
✈️ Air Force One is not just one plane—it’s a term used for any @usairforce aircraft carrying the President. 
✈️ Because the President may need to travel to the furthest locations at any given time, Air Force One is capable of refueling midair giving it unlimited range.
✈️ Air Force One is a technological marvel! These aircraft are equipped with advanced secure communications equipment, allowing the aircraft to function as a mobile command center in the event of an emergency.
✈️ Can you say spacious? Air Force One has over 4,000 square feet of floor space on three levels, including an extensive suite for the President, a conference room, a medical suite that can function as an operating room, and two food preparation galleys that can feed 100 people at a time.

How’s this for #MondayMotivation? 

As the first living and the first enlisted Airman to be awarded the Medal of Honor, SSgt Maynard “Snuffy” Smith was not your typical hero. But on May 1, 1943, he proved that true heroes don’t require a resumé, just the opportunity to prove what they’re made of.

The @usairforce Warrior Medics have stepped up to the plate once again in the fight against COVID-19. The Wilford Hall pathology lab is conducting its own testing on samples taken from patients suspected of having the illness. On the fence about getting the COVID-19 Vaccine? Let’s play a game of myth or fact.

❌ MYTH: If I’ve already had COVID-19, I don’t need a vaccine.
✅ FACT: You may still benefit from getting the vaccine even if you’ve previously gotten sick with COVID-19.

❌ MYTH: Getting the COVID-19 vaccine gives you COVID-19.
✅ FACT: The vaccine for COVID-19 cannot and will not give you COVID-19. 

❌ MYTH: The COVID-19 vaccine can affect women’s fertility.
✅ FACT: The COVID-19 vaccine will not affect fertility. 

Understanding how vaccinations work and getting the #COVID19 vaccine are the first steps we can all take to end the pandemic.

For the @spaceforcedod, every day is an opportunity to reach new heights. 

Last month, the Space Force had its first-ever rapid response launch, Tactically Responsive Launch-2 (TacRL-2). A demonstration of speed, agility, and flexibility, TacRL-2’s mission was to set up a satellite that increased space domain awareness—or detect artificial objects in orbit. 

Missions like these will continue to propel the Space Force into the future and establish its place in the space domain.

A day in the life of an @af_academy cadet: 
🕕 6:30 a.m.: Rise & Shine ☀️
🕗 8:30 a.m.: Class, Formation, Flight Training (and more).
🕚 11:30 a.m.: Read @georgehtakei’s new book! 

Air Force Academy cadets from the class of 2025 will get the chance to read Takei’s best-seller “They Called Us Enemy” as a part of the Air Force Academy’s new reading initiative. 

The graphic novel, which reveals a look into Takei’s experience growing up in an internment camp during World War II, aims to educate the cadets on the histories of our country, and furthermore, inspire them to fight against cruelty and injustice.
